.. DA/DB have been exhausted... I fall off the ramp again to the floor... I can see the exit and my group, but I'm not gonna make it....<P>Darianne is covered by a soft glow (Cel Heal'd myself)<P>The spider is coming down the ramp, it did not fall off and come to me, so I got t he heal off... then I start running to my group....<P>Uncon...<P>Up!<P>Uncon...<P>Up!<P>Uncon...<P>Dead<P>Cel Heal makes for the best near neath, then death experiences.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>This is no where as cool as your CoH story, loved it.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kaharz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">This happened to my low lvl rogue<P>Fighting with a group in the large elite room in BB.  Someone pulls when they shouldn't, room starts popping too, druid runs away (nothing even agroed on him) one tank dies, the other starts looting in the middle of fight (typical newb group) so really only me and the ranger are fighting.<P>I fall unconcious, the ranger heals me, I regain conciousness.  This happens roughly 11 times.  Finally the other warrior stops looting and jumps in.  But just as he does I die, before "Loading please wait" comes up I see the last gnoll die too.  On more little crappy ranger heal and I would have survived after being knocked out around 12 times<P>Kaharz Stronginthearm<BR>45th lvl cleric of Brell<BR>Rodcet Nife<BR>Flames of Faradhim<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tailchaser</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The death that got the longest uncontrollable laughing fit out of our regular group:<P>Back in the mid 30's, hunting in Cazic.  Respawn stacks on a big pull, we get in a bad situation, and call evac.  Wizard starts the evac, I throw a group heal, then start covering him so he doesn't get interrupted.  9 seconds...6 seconds...3 seconds...and the evac goes off, with everyone still alive!  I breathe a sigh of relief, and wait to zone.  The rest of the group pops up...all except the Wizard.<P>Y'know how evacs have a really really really small chance to leave people behind?<P>His own evac left him behind, and he died.<P>He couldn't play for the next few minutes because he was laughing so hard he couldn't type.<P>My wife also got a guildmate killed in Firona Vie recently.  He's a 30ish Enchanter who was working on his Illusion:Iksar quest, and she's a L52 Ranger who went to help him out.  She was leading him to the outpost...and walked off the edge of the cliff as she was talking to someone.  She survived the falling damage.  He didn't.  She was grovelling at him for days.  He was quite amused.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corii Se'Lune</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Playing with a friend from Australia (Paladin) in the Hole. This was way back before Velious. Anyway, I was ucing CH, and it was going pretty well. Timing was going great until I see this:<P>Jimako is completely healed.<BR>Jimako died.<P>WTF!<P>So res, keep going... bi fight, almost got em all dead...<P>Jimako is completely healed.<BR>Jimako died.<P>ARGH! I got so disgusted I stopped using CH the rest of the night. Turned out his wacky Aussie connection was lagging badly, and his system wasn't registering the complete heals fast enough. We still laugh about it.  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Corii Se'Lune<BR>Devoted of Quellious<BR>56th Rank Templar<BR><A HREF="http://succoringwinds.ipeasy.com" TARGET=_blank> Succoring Winds </A>- Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thistleburr</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Greetings!<P>Fighting Druushk in a bit of server-side lag...<P>Oneton feels a touch of redemption<BR>You feel a touch of redemption<BR>Chuut feels a to