l on the chanter to keep him alive long enough to mez again, if needed i cast a quick remedy on him if he is being beaten on too hard to help with the celes healing.<P>At this point, our chanter is at 3 1/2 bubs of life with a celes heal on him. He begins to regen when we discover he is nowhere to be found.    <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>A few seconds go by, and the chanter comes running back up to the group from down below. "I was knocked off" he says. No biggie, these things happen. <P>We kill 3 more mobs, one breaks and the chanter is getting beat on again. Once again i cast celes heal, and nothing happens. I cast remedy and nothing happens, his life does not move. <P>This boggles me as i do not know why i can cast on him and him not get life back. <P>We all have to zone as the rest of the mobs break Dazzle and commence to tear into us, me being the target seeing how is the chanter is not around.<P>We all jump off the tower and swim for our lives, and we make it to the zone with out any deaths.<P>I ask the chanter what happened? He replies "I was knocked off 2 more times and i had to run back to T2" <P>Well no wonder we had 7 or so mobs on us. He brought some friends everytime he came, not to mention when i tried to heal him, he was in the water, which not only wasted my mana, but it didn't heal him even though it was casted on him.    <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif"><P>It was funny when i thought about it. Seeing a chanter fall off of a ledge, run back up to crowd control, fall off again, then repeat several times.<P>Reminded me of something off of Monty Python :P<P>Sorry if this was too long, I hope there is some humor in this for someone besides me.<P>[This message has been edited by Sylvus (edited 03-16-2001).]<p>[This message has been edited by Sylvus (edited 03-16-2001).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Themis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verd