een 15 little spiders running toward me.<P>So I took off and ran towards the zone into the city to get the 2 other gaurds to help out in the killing.  I ran past them and spun around, seeing the delightful message that these spiders were all being slain.<P>Satisfied that they were all dead, I ran back out into the opening to be greeted by...<BR>You have been slain by Cargo Clockwork<P>DOH!  He might have been mechanical, but he's still in cahoots with the little organic spiders!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have 2 REALLY memerable life and death stories.<P>It was in Najena. I was a tad low for the zone, but was doing ok with a group zone fighting. Anyways, someone trains some tenticle terrors to the zone. I always run and jump as I run to get the little edge in front. As I got to the zone, I jump, and got nailed by the train. I actually saw myself do the "dwarf roll" from above as I went unconsious, and saw "LOADING, PLEASE WAIT". I thought I was dead, but I zoned out and was bleeding to death. Someone used a bandage on me to bring me back to life.<P>Another one that I LOVE was when I was in the Ghost room of Unrest. One of the group members was new ans wanted to look into the Pit. He fell off and aggroed everything. TRAIN TO ZONE! I was running my ass off as the group was getting ground down. I reached the top of the stairs and stopped to DA. DA on, but I get stunned. The group passed me and I was "IT". I made it to the front door and a TT did that Tenticle Throwback spell that shot me over my group, across the courtyard and slammed me into the wall over the tunnel out. That probably saved my life  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> I bounced off the wall and kept running.<P>Made it to the zone with like 20kp left. I was the butt of many "flying dwarf" jokes for awhile after that.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD val